---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'GeoBlue in Portugal', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-compliance', text: 'D7/D8 Visa Compliance', level: 2 },
  { id: 'portugal-network', text: 'Network Coverage in Portugal', level: 2 },
  { id: 'plans-and-pricing', text: 'Plans and Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'blue-cross-advantage', text: 'Blue Cross Advantage', level: 2 },
  { id: 'sns-transition', text: 'Transitioning to SNS', level: 2 },
  { id: 'who-its-for', text: 'Who Should Choose GeoBlue', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Health Insurance in Portugal', href: '/countries/portugal/insurance' },
  { title: 'GeoBlue Review', href: '/providers/geoblue' },
  { title: 'GeoBlue vs Aetna', href: '/compare/aetna-international-vs-geoblue' },
];

const planColumns = [
  { key: 'plan', header: 'Plan' },
  { key: 'coverage', header: 'Coverage' },
  { key: 'portugalPrice', header: 'Portugal (Age 35)' },
  { key: 'visaCompliant', header: 'Visa Compliant' },
];

const planRows = [
  { plan: 'Voyager Essential', coverage: 'Inpatient + Emergency', portugalPrice: '$170-230/mo', visaCompliant: 'Check requirements' },
  { plan: 'Voyager Choice', coverage: 'Essential + Outpatient', portugalPrice: '$230-300/mo', visaCompliant: true },
  { plan: 'Voyager Excel', coverage: 'Comprehensive + Maternity', portugalPrice: '$300-400/mo', visaCompliant: true },
];

const comparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'factor', header: 'Factor' },
  { key: 'geoblue', header: 'GeoBlue' },
  { key: 'portuguese', header: 'Portuguese Insurers' },
];

const comparisonRows = [
  { factor: 'Monthly Cost (Age 35)', geoblue: '$230-300', portuguese: '€26-80' },
  { factor: 'US Network', geoblue: 'Blue Cross (96% of hospitals)', portuguese: 'Not available' },
  { factor: 'Coverage Outside Portugal', geoblue: 'Worldwide', portuguese: 'Limited' },
  { factor: 'Network in Portugal', geoblue: 'Good (major cities)', portuguese: 'Extensive' },
  { factor: 'Mobile App', geoblue: 'Excellent', portuguese: 'Varies' },
  { factor: 'Portability', geoblue: 'Fully portable', portuguese: 'Must cancel' },
  { factor: 'Best For', geoblue: 'US expats wanting BCBS', portuguese: 'Long-term residents' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="GeoBlue Health Insurance in Portugal"
  description="Guide to using GeoBlue in Portugal. Blue Cross network for US expats. D7/D8 visa compliance, Portuguese network, and pricing details."
  headline="GeoBlue Health Insurance in Portugal"
  subheadline="Blue Cross Blue Shield's international arm. Keep your familiar US network while enjoying life in Portugal."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/countries/portugal-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get a GeoBlue Portugal Quote"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/geoblue"
>
  <h2 id="overview">GeoBlue in Portugal</h2>
  <p>
    GeoBlue is Blue Cross Blue Shield's international insurance brand, designed specifically for Americans living abroad. For the growing community of US expats in Portugal—retirees on D7 visas, digital nomads on D8 visas, and families seeking a new life—GeoBlue offers continuity with the healthcare network they already know.
  </p>
  <p>
    When you fly home to visit family or need care from US specialists, your GeoBlue card works at the same Blue Cross hospitals and doctors used by over 100 million Americans. No surprise networks, no coverage gaps.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">96%</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">US hospitals in network</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">1.7M+</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">International providers</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">190+</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Countries covered</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Get a Portugal-Specific Quote"
    description="See what GeoBlue costs for Americans in Portugal."
    buttonText="Get Quote"
    buttonHref="/go/geoblue"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="visa-compliance">D7/D8 Visa Compliance</h2>
  <p>
    GeoBlue plans can meet Portuguese visa requirements. As a US-based insurer, some consulates may require additional documentation compared to EU-regulated alternatives.
  </p>

  <h3>Portuguese Visa Insurance Requirements</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>D7 (Passive Income Visa):</strong> Health insurance covering Portugal</li>
    <li><strong>D8 (Digital Nomad Visa):</strong> Comprehensive health coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Golden Visa:</strong> Health insurance required</li>
    <li><strong>Student Visa:</strong> Coverage for study duration</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>GeoBlue Documentation</h3>
  <p>
    GeoBlue provides visa documentation including:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Certificate of coverage</li>
    <li>Coverage confirmation letter</li>
    <li>Policy details showing benefits</li>
    <li>Translation assistance available</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Consulate Tip</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800">
      US consulates processing Portuguese visas are generally familiar with GeoBlue. Voyager Choice or Excel plans are best—they include outpatient coverage and meet typical requirements. Request documentation early and confirm with your specific consulate.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="portugal-network">Network Coverage in Portugal</h2>
  <p>
    GeoBlue contracts with 1.7 million+ providers in 190 countries. In Portugal, coverage focuses on major cities and popular expat regions.
  </p>

  <h3>Coverage by Region</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Lisbon:</strong> Strong network including Hospital da Luz, CUF, British Hospital</li>
    <li><strong>Porto:</strong> Multiple hospital and specialist options</li>
    <li><strong>Algarve:</strong> Coverage in Faro, Lagos, Portimão</li>
    <li><strong>Cascais/Estoril:</strong> Popular expat area with good access</li>
    <li><strong>Madeira:</strong> Funchal coverage available</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>GeoBlue Mobile App</h3>
  <p>
    GeoBlue's app is excellent for finding care in Portugal:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>GPS-based provider search</li>
    <li>Filter by specialty and language</li>
    <li>English-speaking doctor finder</li>
    <li>Direct contact and directions</li>
    <li>Digital insurance card</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Out-of-Network Care</h3>
  <p>
    You can see any licensed provider in Portugal. Portuguese private healthcare is affordable—paying out of pocket and claiming reimbursement is straightforward.
  </p>

  <h2 id="plans-and-pricing">Plans and Pricing</h2>
  <p>
    GeoBlue Voyager plans are designed for long-term expats. US coverage is included—not an expensive add-on.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={planColumns} rows={planRows} />
  </div>

  <p>
    <em>Prices include worldwide coverage with full US Blue Cross access.</em>
  </p>

  <h3>Plan Recommendations for Portugal</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Voyager Essential:</strong> Hospital-focused. Pay for routine care out of pocket (affordable in Portugal) or use SNS once registered.</li>
    <li><strong>Voyager Choice:</strong> Most popular. Includes outpatient, meets visa requirements, good balance.</li>
    <li><strong>Voyager Excel:</strong> Comprehensive including maternity. Best for families or those wanting full coverage.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Deductible Strategy</h3>
  <p>
    Portuguese private healthcare is affordable (doctor visits €30-60). Consider:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Higher deductible ($2,500+) to reduce premiums</li>
    <li>Pay routine care out of pocket or use SNS</li>
    <li>Use GeoBlue for hospitals, specialists, US trips</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="blue-cross-advantage">Blue Cross Advantage</h2>
  <p>
    The core reason to choose GeoBlue for Portugal:
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-3">US Network Benefits</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-blue-800">
        <li>96% of US hospitals in network</li>
        <li>Familiar Blue Cross network</li>
        <li>Direct billing—no claims needed</li>
        <li>BCBS negotiated rates</li>
        <li>Keep your US doctors</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Portugal Benefits</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>Family visits to US covered</li>
        <li>US specialists accessible</li>
        <li>Emergency care during trips</li>
        <li>Seamless repatriation coverage</li>
        <li>US prescriptions manageable</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="sns-transition">Transitioning to SNS</h2>
  <p>
    After getting your Portuguese residence permit, you can register for SNS (Serviço Nacional de Saúde)—Portugal's public healthcare system. Many American expats keep GeoBlue even after SNS access.
  </p>

  <h3>Why Keep GeoBlue After SNS?</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>US coverage:</strong> SNS doesn't cover you in America</li>
    <li><strong>Faster access:</strong> Private care vs public waitlists</li>
    <li><strong>English-speaking doctors:</strong> Easier to find privately</li>
    <li><strong>Worldwide travel:</strong> Coverage beyond Portugal/EU</li>
    <li><strong>Portability:</strong> If you move again, coverage continues</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategy</h3>
  <p>
    Once registered for SNS:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Consider higher deductible plan</li>
    <li>Use SNS for routine Portuguese care (it's free since 2022)</li>
    <li>Use GeoBlue for private specialists, US visits, and travel</li>
    <li>Voyager Essential may suffice if SNS handles outpatient</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Blue Cross Coverage in Portugal"
    description="Keep your familiar US network while living abroad."
    buttonText="Get Your Quote"
    buttonHref="/go/geoblue"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="who-its-for">Who Should Choose GeoBlue</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={comparisonColumns} rows={comparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Ideal For</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
        <li>US citizens in Portugal</li>
        <li>Those familiar with Blue Cross</li>
        <li>Expats who visit the US regularly</li>
        <li>People who want largest US network</li>
        <li>Those who value excellent mobile app</li>
        <li>Families with US healthcare ties</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Consider Alternatives</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>Non-US citizens (can't purchase)</li>
        <li>Those who never visit the US</li>
        <li>Budget-conscious (Multicare is cheaper)</li>
        <li>Those wanting EU-regulated insurer</li>
        <li>Settled permanently in Portugal</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <h3>Do I need to be a US citizen for GeoBlue?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes. GeoBlue requires US citizenship or permanent residency with US ties. It's designed specifically for Americans abroad.
  </p>

  <h3>Is GeoBlue accepted for Portuguese D7 visa?</h3>
  <p>
    Generally yes. GeoBlue Voyager Choice or Excel plans meet typical requirements. Confirm with your specific consulate, as requirements can vary.
  </p>

  <h3>How does GeoBlue compare to Aetna International?</h3>
  <p>
    Both are excellent for US expats in Portugal. GeoBlue offers the Blue Cross network; Aetna offers modular Navigator plans. Pricing is similar. <a href="/compare/aetna-international-vs-geoblue">See our detailed comparison</a>.
  </p>

  <h3>Can I use GeoBlue while waiting for SNS?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes. GeoBlue covers you immediately upon enrollment. Use it for all healthcare until your SNS registration completes.
  </p>

  <h3>Should I cancel GeoBlue once I have SNS?</h3>
  <p>
    Consider keeping it if you visit the US, want faster private care, or might relocate. If you're settled permanently and rarely travel to the US, Portuguese insurance may be more cost-effective.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Ready for Portugal?"
    description="Get a personalized GeoBlue quote for your situation."
    buttonText="Get Your Quote"
    buttonHref="/go/geoblue"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Visa requirements and network availability change. Verify all information with GeoBlue and Portuguese authorities before making decisions.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
